  "title": "MRI / CT Radiographer (Private clinic / Central / Office Hours)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Company Profile:</strong></p>\n<p>Established for over 20 years, our advanced private health-screening and diagnostic imaging centre has grown into a trusted provider of preventive healthcare services. We offer <strong>Radiographers specialising in</strong> <strong>MRI and CT</strong> the opportunity to work with modern imaging technology in a supportive, patient-focused environment. In this role, you’ll play a key part in early detection and wellness care, supported by a collaborative team that values professionalism, accuracy, and continuous learning. As we expand our services, we’re seeking dedicated radiography professionals who want to grow their expertise within a stable and forward-looking healthcare organisation.</p>\n<p><strong>Work location: Central</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Work schedule: 5.5 days work week. Monday to Friday and half Sat, office hours</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Perform CT / MRI examinations according to established protocols and safety standards.</li>\n  <li>Prepare and position patients appropriately for imaging procedures, providing clear instructions and reassurance.</li>\n  <li>Operate and maintain CT / MRI equipment, ensuring optimal image quality.</li>\n  <li>Collaborate with radiologists to ensure accurate and timely diagnostic imaging.</li>\n  <li>Maintain accurate patient records, scan logs, and safety documentation.</li>\n  <li>Adhere to radiation safety, infection control, and quality assurance procedures.</li>\n  <li>Assist and support junior staff or students as required.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Key Requirements:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Min. Diploma / Degree in Diagnostic Radiography, Medical Imaging or related fields and must be <strong>AHPC registered</strong>.</li>\n  <li>Min. 3 - 4 years radiography experience in Computed Tomography (CT) / MRI modality preferred.</li>\n  <li>Compassionate and good patient care oriented.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>📩 Your recruiter: <strong>WhatsApp your CV/resume</strong> to<strong> Celine at 8977 7051 </strong>for a quicker response.</p>\n<p>You may also drop your resume via email to <a href=\"mailto:celinechan@envirodynamics.com.sg\">celinechan@envirodynamics.com.sg</a> – only shortlisted candidates will be notified.<br>\n<br>\nCeline Chan I Reg. No: R21103433</p>\n<p>EnviroDynamics Solutions Pte Ltd I EA License No.: 12C6285</p>",
